Cell.Data: Prescription for vision correction products for a patient
An authorization for the supply of glasses and/or contact lenses to a patient.
Business identifier which may be used by other parties to reference or identify the prescription.
ORC-2-Placer Order Number / ORC-3-Filler Order Number
The status of the resource instance.
A link to a resource representing the person to whom the vision products will be supplied.
A link to a resource that identifies the particular occurrence of contact between patient and health care provider.
The date (and perhaps time) when the prescription was written
RXE-32-Original Order Date/Time / ORC-9-Date/Time of Transaction
The healthcare professional responsible for authorizing the prescription

RXE-13-Ordering Provider's DEA Number / RXO-14-Ordering Provider's DEA Number / RXE-14-Pharmacist/Treatment Supplier's Verifier ID / RXO-15-Pharmacist/Treatment Supplier's Verifier ID / ORC-12-Ordering Provider / PRT-5-Participation Person: PRT-4-Participation='OP' (all but last deprecated)
Reason or indication for writing the prescription
Can be the reason or the indication for writing the prescription.
Deals with details of the dispense part of the supply specification.
Identifies the type of vision correction product which is required for the patient.
RXE-2-Give Code / RXO-1-Requested Give Code / RXD-2-Dispense/Give Code
The eye for which the lens applies.
Lens power measured in diopters (0.25 units).
Power adjustment for astigmatism measured in diopters (0.25 units).
Adjustment for astigmatism measured in integer degrees.
Amount of prism to compensate for eye alignment in fractional units.
The relative base, or reference lens edge, for the prism.
Power adjustment for multifocal lenses measured in diopters (0.25 units).
Contact lens power measured in diopters (0.25 units).
Contact lens diameter measured in millimeters.
The recommended maximum wear period for the lens.
Notes for special requirements such as coatings and lens materials.
